    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1969-12-09T15:20:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1969-12-09T15:20:00-05:00" n="25"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d25">
                <head>25. Transcript of a Telephone Conversation Between the President’s Assistant
                    for National Security Affairs (<persName corresp="#p_KHA1">Kissinger</persName>)
                    and Secretary of Defense <persName corresp="#p_LMR1">Laird</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d25fn1">Source: National Archives, <persName
                            corresp="#p_NRM1">Nixon</persName> Presidential Materials, <gloss
                            target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Files, <persName corresp="#p_KHA1"
                            >Kissinger</persName> Telephone Conversation Transcripts, Box 3,
                        Chronological Files. No classification marking.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1969-12-09T15:20:00-05:00">December 9, 1969, 3:20 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_K1">K</gloss> said he has a problem on the oil import
                    business. <gloss target="#t_L1">L</gloss> said so do I. <gloss target="#t_K1"
                        >K</gloss> said this thing has been merrily cooking along and nobody has
                    been paying any attention to the political implications. <gloss target="#t_L1"
                        >L</gloss> said he just went over this with <persName corresp="#p_SBJ1"
                        >Shillito</persName> this morning. <gloss target="#t_K1">K</gloss> said he
                    went over it with <persName corresp="#p_SGP1">Shultz</persName>. <gloss
                        target="#t_K1">K</gloss> said the President hadn’t focused on it before, but
                    now he wants a delay. <gloss target="#t_K1">K</gloss> wondered if <gloss
                        target="#t_L1">L</gloss> and the Joint Chiefs could delay it until the P has
                    focused on it. <gloss target="#t_L1">L</gloss> said sure. <gloss target="#t_K1"
                        >K</gloss> said can you do that? <gloss target="#t_L1">L</gloss> said sure.
                        <gloss target="#t_K1">K</gloss> said he had breakfast with <persName>Rowland
                        Evans</persName>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d25fn2">
                        <persName>Rowland Evans</persName> was a journalist and TV
                        commentator.</note> and he suggested that <gloss target="#t_L1">L</gloss> is
                    the most outstanding man in government. <gloss target="#t_K1">K</gloss> said he
                    fought with him like hell on that issue.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_L1">L</gloss> said on the tariff on the Middle East oil—the
                    Arabs will think we picked them out this time to put a $1.25 tariff on. <gloss
                        target="#t_L1">L</gloss> said they will raise hell. And <gloss
                        target="#t_L1">L</gloss> said our domestic producers are all against it.
                        <gloss target="#t_K1">K</gloss> said there are two issues: tariff against
                    quota and lowering the price of oil. <gloss target="#t_L1">L</gloss> said we
                    shouldn’t put the commission on it; it should be in the White House in <gloss
                        target="#t_OEP1">OEP</gloss>. <gloss target="#t_K1">K</gloss> said what
                    we’ve got to do is get the thing screwed up enough that the P gets some
                    breathing space.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_K1">K</gloss> said he would be seeing <gloss target="#t_L1"
                        >L</gloss> on Thursday; he has a number of things on the <gloss
                        target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> to discuss with <gloss target="#t_L1"
                    >L</gloss>. <gloss target="#t_K1">K</gloss> said he thinks <gloss target="#t_L1"
                        >L</gloss> and <persName corresp="#p_WB1">Bill</persName> should talk 5 or
                    10 minutes about <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> at <gloss
                        target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss>. <gloss target="#t_L1">L</gloss> said make it
                    short, it’s not that significant. <gloss target="#t_K1">K</gloss> said you and I
                    are getting together Thursday morning; there are a number of things on <gloss
                        target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_K1">K</gloss> wanted to talk about.</p>
            </div>
